FBIS3-11055 "drlat052_k_94003" FBIS-LAT-94-052 Document Type:Daily Report 15 Mar 1994 SOUTH AMERICA Argentina Butrus-Ghali Asks Menem To Sign NPT PY1603160394 Buenos Aires LA PRENSA in Spanish 15 Mar 94 p 2 PY1603160394 Buenos Aires LA PRENSA Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] UN Secretary General Butrus Butrus-Ghali yesterday requested of President Carlos Menem that Argentina and Brazil expedite their support for the Nuclear Nonproliferation Treaty [NPT], and also praised the Argentine Government's efforts and constant willingness to send peacemaking forces to conflict regions. Butrus-Ghali said that Argentina has become a leading country in Latin America and, despite his request, noted the efforts it has been making to ratify the nuclear weapon nonproliferation treaty. Menem, in turn, promised to hold talks with Brazil to this end. This information was disclosed by Media Communications Secretary Raul Burzaco at the conclusion of the meeting held between Menem and Butrus-Ghali at Government House. According to Burzaco, Menem and Butrus-Ghali never discussed the possibility of sending 200 Argentine servicemen stationed in Croatia to Bosnia. [passage omitted]
